{
  "doc_id": "54403",
  "text": "Definition 0.9. end (F) is a terminal object in the category of wedges over F. coend (F) is an initial object in the category of cowedges over F. 0.3. subdivision category, existence of coend. [CITATION_1] IX.5] . To a category C we associate its subdivision category C § in the following way: we set Ob C § = Ob (C) ∪ Mor (C) (note that c ∈ C and id c give different objects c § and id § c in C § ). The morphisms are the identity morphisms for the above mentioned objects and also if f ∶ c → d is the morphism in C then it gives rise to the two morphisms c § ",
